<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-583-093  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 583 093.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Nov 5 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>New for IBM: CA upgrades receivables modules. (ComputerAssociates' Accpac Plus Accounts Receivable 6.0) (productannouncement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Buckler, Grant.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Computer Associates International Inc. Computer Associates MicroProducts Div. (Product introduction).andO;Product:   ACCPAC BPI Accounting (Accounting software) (Product enhancement)Accpac Plus Accounts Receivable 6.0 (Accounting software) (Productintroduction).andO;Topic:     Software PublishersProduct IntroductionAccountingFinancial Software.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>NEW FOR IBM: CA Upgrades Receivables Modules  11/05/90 GARDEN CITY, NEW YORK,U.S.A., 1990 NOV 5 (NB) -- Computer Associates has announced upgrades to theaccounts receivable modules of both Accpac Plus and Accpac BPI Accounting.andO;Both upgrades include improved tax collection tracking, including featuresnecessary for handling the Canadian Goods and Services Tax, scheduled to takeeffect January 1.andM;John Schoutsen, marketing manager for business applications software at CA'sVancouver, British Columbia office, said the improved tax tracking featuresarose out of the need to modify both packages to support the new Canadiantax.andP;  An upgrade to Accpac Bedford accounting, CA's entry-level accountingproduct, will appear by year-end to handle the tax, he said.andM;Schoutsen added that while the tax changes are the principal additions toAccpac BPI, the Accpac Plus upgrade is part of a broader plan to add newfeatures to the Accpac Plus product.andP;  The release of Accpac Plus AccountsReceivable 6.0 follows the launch earlier this fall of Version 6.0 of theGeneral Ledger module, he said.andP;  The new versions allow Accpac Plus to recordand report more detailed accounting information than before, he said.andM;(Grant Buckler/19901101/0800PST/Press Contact: Kristin Keyes, ComputerAssociates, 408-922-2310; John Schoutsen, Computer Associates, 604-737-2233)</TEXT></DOC>